<HEAD>Police Posing As Trash Collectors Arrest 16 Suspected Drug Dealers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police officers posed as trash collectors and rode on santitation trucks to gain the confidence of drug dealers in a sting that resulted in 16 arrests. `` Once they saw the uniform and the truck, they trusted us,'' said one of the three undercover officers involved. `` They'd approach us and say, ` You guys want rocks You want a smoke?' We were approached by several ladies of the night who gave us lots of information on the crack houses in the neighborhood.'' The monthlong operation, which ended Thursday, was organized after city sanitation workers told police that they were offered drugs as they made their rounds. The officers said they gamely adjusted to the aroma their disguises required. `` It was just part of the job,'' said one.
