<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> will lay off 56 network staff engineers at its <LOCATION> Burbank </LOCATION> studios in February and June, the network announced Friday. In the first step, 30 engineers will be cut by Feb. 17, and in the sefcond 26 more will be laid off by June 16. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> is offering sizable bonuses to engineers who volunteer for layoff. The cutbacks are in operations and technical services, which supply floor cameramen, lighting directors, technical directors and videotape editors. The layoffs are in addition to a cutback of 90 engineers in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, 24 in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, 13 in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, and three in <LOCATION> Cleveland </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> said the layoffs were the result of innovations in videotape technology.
