warm memories of the film, especially of its star, <PERSON> Sissy </PERSON> <PERSON> Spacek </PERSON>. `` I always felt that the whole movie was a very wonderful experience and it had everything to do with <PERSON> Sissy </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> D'Angelo </PERSON> said. `` She did such special work, and I really think a lot of the atmosphere had to do with that she was such a wonderful person.'' <PERSON> D'Angelo </PERSON> had known director <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON> -LRB- `` <LOCATION> Mona </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lisa </LOCATION>'' -RRB- and quickly agreed to be in `` High Spirits.'' The atmosphere on the set seemed to live up to the film's title. `` There are some scenes where you're watching <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Toole </PERSON>, <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Gallagher </PERSON>, Little <PERSON> John </PERSON> -LRB- a street theater performer from <LOCATION> Dublin </LOCATION> -RRB-, <PERSON> Liam </PERSON> <PERSON> Neeson </PERSON> and me and <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Guttenberg </PERSON>. All these people came together. That was fascinating,'' she said. `` Everybody did have such different approaches. It was a process of being quick on your feet all the time.'' She especially enjoyed working with <PERSON> O'Toole </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Toole </PERSON>'s a genius, and very charming. <PERSON> Peter </PERSON>'s got one of the all-time great reputations for having lived a life so it was a pleasure to see that he's also the ultimate professional.'' `` High Spirits'' has undergone changes since filming was completed. The producers found the plot too complicated and ended up eliminating material. <PERSON> D'Angelo </PERSON> was unhappy with some of the alterations, but still defended the movie. `` This opened the <ORGANIZATION> Dublin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Film </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Festival </ORGANIZATION> and I sat with 2,000 people who really, really enjoyed it,'' <PERSON> D