<HEAD>Oil Prices Mostly Lower After Flirting With $16 Level</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Technical factors and concerns about production have sent crude oil futures sharply lower. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the January contract for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION>, the benchmark grade of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, settled 30 cents lower Thursday at $ 15.44 a barrel, after rising 28 cents on Wednesday. Other contract months also declined. Among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange Thursday, the January contract for wholesale home heating oil closed 0.81 cent lower at 48.08 cents a gallon. The contract had risen 0.29 cent Wednesday. But January unleaded gasoline, which lost 0.59 cent on Wednesday, settled at 43.93 cents a gallon, up 0.17 cent from Wednesday's session <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON>, an energy analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Elders </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said prices started out strong, with the January contract for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION> trading as high as $ 15.97 a barrel. But when the contract failed to pierce the psychologically important $ 16-a-barrel level, a selloff began, he said. `` As the price approached the $ 16 level they -LRB- traders -RRB- found themselves asking themselves whether the market was bullish enough to merit that price,'' <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON> explained. `` They came to the realization that it was not as strong fundamentally.'' <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON> said recent reports of higher-than-expected oil production have concerned many traders.
