<FIRST>r f AM-BeuleyResigns     12-09 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Beuley Resigns,0100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Agriculture Department Inspector General Quits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Beuley </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s inspector general for more than two years, has resigned effective Dec. 26, his office said Friday No plans were announced, except that <PERSON> Beuley </PERSON> expects to go to work in the private sector here. <PERSON> Beuley </PERSON>, 49, became <ORGANIZATION> USDA </ORGANIZATION>'s inspector general, or internal watchdog, in August 1986. He joined the department as deputy in September 1985. Before that he was assistant inspector general for auditing at the <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> for five years and had also served in the Commerce Depaertment.
