<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> on Friday denied speculation that a move to break up the sales force it shares with <ORGANIZATION> Continential </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> is intended to do anything but sell more tickets. `` It has absolutely nothing to do with anything except better customer service and selling our core markets to the public,'' said <PERSON> Cori </PERSON> <PERSON> Zywotow </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> manager of corporate communications marketing. But labor officials said there may be other reasons for the move to separate the two carriers' sales forces, which were combined after <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> bought both airlines. `` It may indicate the company is being readied for sale,'' said <PERSON> J.B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stokes </PERSON>, a spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Line </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pilots </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> has insisted the money-losing airline is not for sale. But speculation increased after real estate magnate <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> negotiated to buy Eastern's most profitable division, the <ORGANIZATION> Northeast </ORGANIZATION> shuttle linking <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, for $ 365 million cash. Eastern lost about $ 234 million in the first nine months of the year and has laid off about 3,500 employees in recent months. Other union officials speculated that the sales change may be an attempt by <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> to keep Miami-based <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> and Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> from being declared one carrier for labor representation purposes. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mediation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> has been addressing that matter in hearings since last summer. Eastern-Continental Sales was formed when the operations were put together to improve efficiency. Its representatives called on travel agents, promoting group packages, charters and special fares offered by the two carriers. `` This was one of the things where we had great consternation when we did it,'' <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s executive vice president and chief operating officer, said Thursday. `` We have felt, and the sales people have told us this, that it's very difficult to sell two products.'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> says the carriers are independent and he has no plans to merge them. He turned the chairmanship of <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> over to <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Corr </PERSON>, former president of <ORGANIZATION> Trans </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, earlier this week. The present sales team will be split in half, <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> said. Each will be based at its carrier's headquarters. Eastern salespeople will report to <PERSON> Stan </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, vice president of passenger sales. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> will report to <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> vice president of marketing <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON>. `` It's really going back and concentrating our energies on Eastern and emphasizing our sales programs and distinctive features,'' <PERSON> Zywotow </PERSON> said. `` And we're expecting that with a dedicated sales force that we can concentrate on our tradtional core markets'' along the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Latin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION>.
