City </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION>; with <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Bristol </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, to demonstrate the recovery of low-sulfur coal particles from a mine waste disposal pond at <LOCATION> Logan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> W. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>; and with <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> to upgrade western coals by reducing moisture and sulfur content at <LOCATION> Colstrip </LOCATION>, Mont. The clean coal program is aimed at financing $ 5 billion worth of projects over five years, at least half the money to come from non-federal sources.
