<HEAD>Major Independents Join Forces</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two major computer software companies, <ORGANIZATION> Duquesne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Morino </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, said Friday they will merge into one of the industry's largest independent companies. `` Our merger represents the first true merger in our industry, one which brings together two companies with comparable histories, successes and operating philosophies,'' they said in a joint statement. Both serve the growing market for programs for larger <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> and compatible mainframe computers. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Morino </PERSON>, chairman of the <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> company, will become chairman of the new concern, and <ORGANIZATION> Duquesne </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Glen </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Chatfield </PERSON> will become chief executive. The combined firm, for which a name was not announced, will be valued at about $ 400 million, with 600 employees generating annual sales of about $ 100 million. The new company will have cash of nearly $ 60 million and no debt. `` We'll be attractively positioned for both internal development and external expansion,'' the two chairmen said. <ORGANIZATION> Duquesne </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Morino </PERSON> will maintain their present headquarters. They proposed merging no later than March 31 in a stock swap, pending approval of their boards and shareholders. <ORGANIZATION> Duquesne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION> was founded in 1970 and over the last five years has grown at a rate of 60 percent compounded annually, with 1988 revenue of $ 50.3 million. <PERSON> Morino </PERSON> began developing software for other vendors in 1973 and by June 30, 1988, had reached $ 44.7 million in revenue.
