<HEAD>Oil Prices Rebound</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For Saturday PMs</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 After a volatile week, oil futures prices finished on a strong note. `` The market closed at one of its highest levels in a long time,'' said <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Redoglia </PERSON>, a trader with <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION>. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the January contract for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION>, the benchmark grade of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, settled 40 cents higher Friday at $ 15.84 cents a barrel, after falling 30 cents on Thursday during a technical selloff. The contract had been up and down throughout the week. Other contract months also gained ground Friday. Among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange, the January contract for wholesale home heating oil closed 1.42 cents higher at 49.50 cents a gallon. The contract had fallen 0.81 cent on Thursday. Traders said seasonal demand was responsible for the sharp price increase. January unleaded gasoline, which gained 0.17 cent in the previous session, settled at 44.46 cents a gallon, up 0.53 cent. <PERSON> Redoglia </PERSON> said there was `` no real news, no real fundamental reason'' for Friday's rally. `` Except there's a feeling the market can work higher if <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> sticks to its quotas,'' he said. In late November, the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION> reached a production agreement aimed at propping up sagging worldwide oil prices.
